FAQs
Why should I study medicine in Georgia?
Georgia offers high-quality medical education, affordable tuition fees, and a supportive learning environment. The comprehensive curriculum and hands-on clinical training prepare students for successful medical careers.

How can Qadri-International assist me in applying to Georgian medical universities?
Qadri-International provides personalized counseling, application assistance, visa support, financial planning, and pre-departure and post-arrival services to ensure your success in applying to Georgian medical universities.

What are the advantages of studying in an international environment?
Studying in an international environment exposes you to diverse cultures and perspectives, enriching your educational experience and preparing you for a global medical career.

Are the medical programs in Georgia taught in English?
Yes, many universities in Georgia offer medical programs taught in English, making them accessible for international students and ensuring a smooth educational experience.

What kind of clinical training do Georgian medical universities provide?
Georgian medical universities emphasize hands-on clinical training, allowing students to gain practical experience in affiliated hospitals and clinics and work alongside experienced medical professionals.
